Hi Martina, 

We can create the forms for you on the website. This way they can sit directly within the event page (or any page you like).

The submissions will be stored in the backend of the website and can be exported to a spreadsheet when needed. Optionally, you can also receive an email each time someone submits.

Does that work for you? 

Alternatively, you can still use JotForm and just link off to it as needed.

action.text: Rica Rosario Valencia assigned to Heath Maguire

full_threads.body:
Hi


Please advise the best programme for me to use to create a form that we want to use at 2 upcoming events to collect potential customers' contact details. These customers will be interested in our Disability Services accommodation vacancies.


In the past I have used JotForm for this but am wondering whether it would be better to use a different programme so that the data automatically feeds into our website's database or can this be done via JotForm?


Thank you very much.
